from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, StratifiedKFold
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, roc_auc_score
import xgboost as xgb
dataset=pd.read_csv(r'D:\1work\1 PhD\MLPPCP\Demo_algae.csv')
X = dataset.drop('algae', axis=1)
X.fillna(0, inplace=True) 
y = dataset['algae']
feature_names = X.columns.tolist()
scaler = StandardScaler()
X= scaler.fit_transform(X)
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=57, stratify=y)
smote = SMOTE(sampling_strategy='auto', random_state=551)
X_train_resampled, y_train_resampled = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
X_train = pd.DataFrame(X_train_resampled, columns=feature_names)
y_train = y_train_resampled
X_test = pd.DataFrame(X_test, columns=feature_names)
finxgb = xgb.XGBClassifier(n_estimators=150, learning_rate=0.02, max_depth=6, random_state=80,
                           gamma=0, subsample=1,
                           colsample_bytree=1, min_child_weight=1,
                           use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss')

finxgb.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_train_pred = finxgb.predict(X_train)
y_train_pred_proba = finxgb.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1]
train_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
train_precision = precision_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
train_recall = recall_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
train_f1 = f1_score(y_train, y_train_pred)
train_roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_train, y_train_pred_proba)
train_conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_train, y_train_pred)

train_sensitivity = train_recall
train_specificity = train_conf_matrix[0, 0] / (train_conf_matrix[0, 0] + train_conf_matrix[0, 1])

y_pred = finxgb.predict(X_test)
y_pred_proba = finxgb.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

test_accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
test_precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
test_recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
test_f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
test_roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_proba)
test_conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)

test_sensitivity = test_recall
test_specificity = test_conf_matrix[0, 0] / (test_conf_matrix[0, 0] + test_conf_matrix[0, 1])
print("Training set performance:")
print(f"Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}")
print(f"Sensitivity: {train_sensitivity:.4f}")
print(f"Specificity: {train_specificity:.4f}")
print(f"ROC-AUC: {train_roc_auc:.4f}")

print(f"Accuracy: {test_accuracy:.4f}")

#draw the ROC curve
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
finxgb.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_test_pred_proba = finxgb.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1] 
plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Times New Roman'
plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 12
fpr_test, tpr_test, thresholds_test = roc_curve(y_test, y_test_pred_proba)
roc_auc_test = auc(fpr_test, tpr_test)
plt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))
plt.plot(fpr_test, tpr_test, color='darkorange', lw=2,
         label=f'ROC curve (area = {roc_auc_test:.2f})')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='navy', lw=2, linestyle='--')
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic (ROC)')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, precision_recall_curve

def calculate_sensitivity_specificity(y_true, y_proba, thresholds):
    sensitivity = []
    specificity = []
    for thresh in thresholds:
        y_pred_thresh = (y_proba >= thresh).astype(int)
        conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred_thresh)
        tn, fp, fn, tp = conf_matrix.ravel()
        sens = tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) > 0 else 0
        spec = tn / (tn + fp) if (tn + fp) > 0 else 0
        sensitivity.append(sens)
        specificity.append(spec)
    return sensitivity, specificity
fpr, tpr, roc_thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba)
thresholds = np.linspace(0, 1, 100) 
sensitivity, specificity = calculate_sensitivity_specificity(y_test, y_pred_proba, thresholds)
best_threshold_idx = np.argmin(np.abs(np.array(sensitivity) - np.array(specificity)))
best_threshold = thresholds[best_threshold_idx]
print(f"Best threshold where Sensitivity == Specificity: {best_threshold:.4f}")
print(f"At this threshold: Sensitivity = {sensitivity[best_threshold_idx]:.4f}, Specificity = {specificity[best_threshold_idx]:.4f}")
plt.figure(figsize=(5, 4)) 
plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Times New Roman'
plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 14
plt.plot(thresholds, sensitivity, label="Sensitivity", color="blue", linewidth=2)
plt.plot(thresholds, specificity, label="Specificity", color="green", linewidth=2)
plt.axvline(x=best_threshold, color="red", linestyle="--", label=f"Best Threshold = {best_threshold:.4f}")
plt.xlabel("Threshold", fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel("Score", fontsize=14)
plt.title("Sensitivity and Specificity vs. Threshold", fontsize=16)
plt.legend(fontsize=14)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Best threshold where Sensitivity == Specificity: 0.2424
At this threshold: Sensitivity = 0.8462, Specificity = 0.8493

#Map the global risk
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
predY_df = pd.read_csv(r'D:\1work\1 PhD\MLPPCP\predicted_results_algae_custom_threshold.csv')
shapefile_path = r'D:\1work\1 PhD\Gis test\globalriver2km.shp'
gdf = gpd.read_file(shapefile_path)
contient_shapefile_path = r'D:\1work\1 PhD\Gis test\contient.shp'
contient_gdf = gpd.read_file(contient_shapefile_path)
if 'level' in gdf.columns:
    gdf = gdf.drop(columns=['level'])
if 'probably' in gdf.columns:
    gdf = gdf.drop(columns=['probably'])
if 'Id' not in predY_df.columns or 'probably' not in predY_df.columns:
    raise ValueError("The CSV file must contain 'Id' and 'probably' columns.")
merged_gdf = gdf.merge(predY_df, on='Id', how='left')
if 'probably' not in merged_gdf.columns:
    raise ValueError("The merge operation failed")
gdf_green = merged_gdf[(merged_gdf['probably'] >= 0) & (merged_gdf['probably'] < 0.2424)]
gdf_yellow = merged_gdf[(merged_gdf['probably'] >= 0.2424) & (merged_gdf['probably'] < 0.5)]
gdf_orange = merged_gdf[(merged_gdf['probably'] >= 0.5) & (merged_gdf['probably'] < 0.75)]
gdf_red = merged_gdf[(merged_gdf['probably'] >= 0.75) & (merged_gdf['probably'] <= 1)]
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(10, 12), dpi=400)
contient_gdf.plot(ax=ax, color='none', edgecolor='gray', linewidth=0.5, label='Continent')
if not gdf_green.empty:
    gdf_green.plot(ax=ax, color='#00FF00', edgecolor='#00FF00', linewidth=1, label='0-0.2424')
if not gdf_yellow.empty:
    gdf_yellow.plot(ax=ax, color='yellow', edgecolor='yellow', linewidth=1, label='0.2424-0.5')
if not gdf_orange.empty:
    gdf_orange.plot(ax=ax, color='orange', edgecolor='orange', linewidth=1, label='0.5-0.75')
if not gdf_red.empty:
    gdf_red.plot(ax=ax, color='red', edgecolor='red', linewidth=1, label='0.75-1')
plt.legend()
ax.set_aspect('equal')
plt.show()
